Regulatory Affairs Manager GNE
- ,
Date Posted: 2014/05/06 07:03:34
Ref. JB3047724
Job Description
The new role is will act as a manager for the GNE regulatory affairs team in the Dubai office.
As this is a leadership role only successful candidates with a
4 to 5 year track record in regulatory and 1 to 2 years in management will be considered.
It is essential for the role you come from a
respected pharmaceutical multinational company and have good working knowledge in regulatory of the GNE countries. There are no exceptions.
Skills
Plus having a pharmaceutical degree you will be fluent in English both written and verbal. A second language is beneficial, ideally, Arabic, French or Urdu.
Previous working knowledge in regulatory for labeling and variations is a must.
You will clearly demonstrate management skills, and have at least one to two years managing a team. My client is looking for people with strong interpersonal skills, excellent leadership and motivational skills.
This role requires a strategic thinker, detail oriented, strong focus on time lines and a genuine love of regulatory.
Computer skills:
It is essential you are efficient on Word, Excel, Power Point & Adobe Acrobat
My client offers an excellent career path and international travel.
Education
Pharmaceutical Degree
